source.name: 2001 Small Area Health Insurance Estimates (SAHIE)
source.description: The Census Bureau's Small Area Health Insurance Estimates (SAHIE) program produces estimates of health insurance coverage for states and all counties. These data are 2001 estimates of health insurance coverage for women by age, race, Hispanic origin, and income categories at the state level.
